      <p>To float images just add the class img-left of img-right and it will float the image and apply the appropriate margins to the image too. If you want your images to be 100% just add the class img-max and it will become 100% the width of the parent element and height auto to the width.</p>
      <p>For videos all you need to do is wrap your iframe with an element that has the class media and your image will become 100% of it's parent element.</p>
